cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.IT

The paper discusses the lottery ticket hypothesis, which is a concept related to neural networks and their training. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the performance of neural networks with random weights, which falls under the category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also mentions the accuracy of the subnetworks, which is a concept related to computer vision, and hence, cs.CV (Computer Vision) is another likely category. The paper also discusses the over-parameterization of neural networks, which is a concept related to artificial intelligence, and hence, cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another likely category. Finally, the paper discusses the distribution of weights, which is a concept related to information theory, and hence, cs.IT (Information Theory) is another likely category.
